#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn3.25"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.25:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.25:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga "
msgstr "3. Kosala "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 25. Pabbatūpamasutta → pabbatopamasuttaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn3.25:0.3"
msgid "25. Pabbatūpamasutta "
msgstr "25. The Simile of the Mountain "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.225, sc1
msgctxt "sn3.25:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.25:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "King Pasenadi of Kosala sat to one side, and the Buddha said to him, "

msgctxt "sn3.25:1.3"
msgid "“handa kuto nu tvaṃ, mahārāja, āgacchasi divā divassā”ti? "
msgstr "“So, great king, where are you coming from in the middle of the day?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.25:1.4"
msgid "“Yāni tāni, bhante, raññaṃ khattiyānaṃ muddhāvasittānaṃ issariyamadamattānaṃ kāmagedhapariyuṭṭhitānaṃ janapadatthāvariyappattānaṃ mahantaṃ pathavimaṇḍalaṃ abhivijiya ajjhāvasantānaṃ rājakaraṇīyāni bhavanti, tesu khvāhaṃ, etarahi ussukkamāpanno”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, there are anointed aristocratic kings who are infatuated with authority, and obsessed with greed for sensual pleasures. They have attained stability in the country, occupying a vast conquered territory. Today I have been busy fulfilling the duties of such kings.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.101, pts2ed1.226, sc2
msgctxt "sn3.25:2.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, "
msgstr "“What do you think, great king? "

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.2"
msgid "idha te puriso āgaccheyya puratthimāya disāya saddhāyiko paccayiko. "
msgstr "Suppose a trustworthy and reliable man were to come from the east. "

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.3"
msgid "So taṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "He’d approach you and say: "

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.4"
msgid "‘yagghe, mahārāja, jāneyyāsi, ahaṃ āgacchāmi puratthimāya disāya. "
msgstr "‘Please sir, you should know this. I come from the east. "

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.5"
msgid "Tatthaddasaṃ mahantaṃ pabbataṃ abbhasamaṃ, sabbe pāṇe nippothento āgacchati. "
msgstr "There I saw a huge mountain that reached the clouds. And it was coming this way, crushing all creatures. "

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.6"
msgid "Yaṃ te, mahārāja, karaṇīyaṃ, taṃ karohī’ti. "
msgstr "So then, great king, do what you must!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.25:2.7"
msgid "Atha dutiyo puriso āgaccheyya pacchimāya disāya … pe … "
msgstr "Then a second trustworthy and reliable man were to come from the west … "

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.8"
msgid "atha tatiyo puriso āgaccheyya uttarāya disāya … "
msgstr "a third from the north … "

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.9"
msgid "atha catuttho puriso āgaccheyya dakkhiṇāya disāya saddhāyiko paccayiko. "
msgstr "and a fourth from the south. "

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.10"
msgid "So taṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "He’d approach you and say: "

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.11"
msgid "‘yagghe, mahārāja, jāneyyāsi, ahaṃ āgacchāmi dakkhiṇāya disāya. "
msgstr "‘Please sir, you should know this. I come from the south. "

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.12"
msgid "Tatthaddasaṃ mahantaṃ pabbataṃ abbhasamaṃ sabbe pāṇe nippothento āgacchati. "
msgstr "There I saw a huge mountain that reached the clouds. And it was coming this way, crushing all creatures. "

msgctxt "sn3.25:2.13"
msgid "Yaṃ te, mahārāja, karaṇīyaṃ taṃ karohī’ti. "
msgstr "So then, great king, do what you must!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: manussakkhaye → manussakāye (mr)
msgctxt "sn3.25:2.14"
msgid "Evarūpe te, mahārāja, mahati mahabbhaye samuppanne dāruṇe manussakkhaye dullabhe manussatte kimassa karaṇīyan”ti? "
msgstr "Should such a dire threat arise—a terrible loss of human life, when human birth is so rare—what would you do?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn3.25:3.1"
msgid "“Evarūpe me, bhante, mahati mahabbhaye samuppanne dāruṇe manussakkhaye dullabhe manussatte kimassa karaṇīyaṃ aññatra dhammacariyāya aññatra samacariyāya aññatra kusalakiriyāya aññatra puññakiriyāyā”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, what could I do but practice the teachings, practice morality, doing skillful and good actions?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.102, pts2ed1.227, sc4
msgctxt "sn3.25:4.1"
msgid "“Ārocemi kho te, mahārāja, paṭivedemi kho te, mahārāja, adhivattati kho taṃ, mahārāja, jarāmaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "“I tell you, great king, I announce to you: old age and death are advancing upon you. "

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.2"
msgid "Adhivattamāne ce te, mahārāja, jarāmaraṇe kimassa karaṇīyan”ti? "
msgstr "Since old age and death are advancing upon you, what would you do?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.25:4.3"
msgid "“Adhivattamāne ca me, bhante, jarāmaraṇe kimassa karaṇīyaṃ aññatra dhammacariyāya samacariyāya kusalakiriyāya puññakiriyāya? "
msgstr "“Sir, what can I do but practice the teachings, practice morality, doing skillful and good actions? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.25:4.4"
msgid "Yāni tāni, bhante, raññaṃ khattiyānaṃ muddhāvasittānaṃ issariyamadamattānaṃ kāmagedhapariyuṭṭhitānaṃ janapadatthāvariyappattānaṃ mahantaṃ pathavimaṇḍalaṃ abhivijiya ajjhāvasantānaṃ hatthiyuddhāni bhavanti; "
msgstr "Sir, there are anointed aristocratic kings who are infatuated with authority, and obsessed with greed for sensual pleasures. They have attained stability in the country, occupying a vast conquered territory. Such kings engage in battles of elephants, "

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.5"
msgid "tesampi, bhante, hatthiyuddhānaṃ natthi gati natthi visayo adhivattamāne jarāmaraṇe. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.6"
msgid "Yānipi tāni, bhante, raññaṃ khattiyānaṃ muddhāvasittānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.7"
msgid "ajjhāvasantānaṃ assayuddhāni bhavanti … pe … "
msgstr "cavalry, "

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.8"
msgid "rathayuddhāni bhavanti … pe … "
msgstr "chariots, "

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.9"
msgid "pattiyuddhāni bhavanti; "
msgstr "or infantry. "

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.10"
msgid "tesampi, bhante, pattiyuddhānaṃ natthi gati natthi visayo adhivattamāne jarāmaraṇe. "
msgstr "But there is no place, no scope for such battles when old age and death are advancing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: pahonti → yesaṃ honti (mr)
msgctxt "sn3.25:4.11"
msgid "Santi kho pana, bhante, imasmiṃ rājakule mantino mahāmattā, ye pahonti āgate paccatthike mantehi bhedayituṃ. "
msgstr "In this royal court there are ministers of wise counsel who are capable of dividing an approaching enemy by wise counsel. "

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.12"
msgid "Tesampi, bhante, mantayuddhānaṃ natthi gati natthi visayo adhivattamāne jarāmaraṇe. "
msgstr "But there is no place, no scope for such diplomatic battles when old age and death are advancing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: bhumigata and vehasattha are stock in this phrase. they’re explained in Pj2 as “underground” (assuming that bhumigata and bhumatta are synonyms) and “above the ground”.
msgctxt "sn3.25:4.13"
msgid "Saṃvijjati kho pana, bhante, imasmiṃ rājakule pahūtaṃ hiraññasuvaṇṇaṃ bhūmigatañceva vehāsaṭṭhañca, yena mayaṃ pahoma āgate paccatthike dhanena upalāpetuṃ. "
msgstr "In this royal court there is abundant gold coin and bullion stored in dungeons and towers. Using this wealth we can pay off an approaching enemy. "

msgctxt "sn3.25:4.14"
msgid "Tesampi, bhante, dhanayuddhānaṃ natthi gati natthi visayo adhivattamāne jarāmaraṇe. "
msgstr "But there is no place, no scope for such monetary battles when old age and death are advancing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.25:4.15"
msgid "Adhivattamāne ca me, bhante, jarāmaraṇe kimassa karaṇīyaṃ aññatra dhammacariyāya samacariyāya kusalakiriyāya puññakiriyāyā”ti? "
msgstr "When old age and death are advancing, what can I do but practice the teachings, practice morality, doing skillful and good actions?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn3.25:5.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, mahārāja, evametaṃ, mahārāja. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, great king! That’s so true! "

msgctxt "sn3.25:5.2"
msgid "Adhivattamāne jarāmaraṇe kimassa karaṇīyaṃ aññatra dhammacariyāya samacariyāya kusalakiriyāya puññakiriyāyā”ti? "
msgstr "When old age and death are advancing, what can you do but practice the teachings, practice morality, doing skillful and good actions?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.25:5.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn3.25:5.4"
msgid "satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn3.25:6.1"
msgid "“Yathāpi selā vipulā, "
msgstr "“Suppose there were vast mountains "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:6.2"
msgid "nabhaṃ āhacca pabbatā; "
msgstr "of solid rock touching the sky "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:6.3"
msgid "Samantānupariyāyeyyuṃ, "
msgstr "drawing in from all sides "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:6.4"
msgid "nippothento catuddisā. "
msgstr "and crushing the four quarters. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn3.25:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ jarā ca maccu ca, "
msgstr "So too old age and death "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: pāṇine → pāṇino (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn3.25:7.2"
msgid "adhivattanti pāṇine; "
msgstr "advance upon all living creatures—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:7.3"
msgid "Khattiye brāhmaṇe vesse, "
msgstr "aristocrats, brahmins, merchants, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:7.4"
msgid "sudde caṇḍālapukkuse; "
msgstr "workers, outcastes, and scavengers. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Na kiñci → na kañci (?)
msgctxt "sn3.25:7.5"
msgid "Na kiñci parivajjeti, "
msgstr "They spare nothing. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:7.6"
msgid "sabbamevābhimaddati. "
msgstr "They crush all beneath them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn3.25:8.1"
msgid "Na tattha hatthīnaṃ bhūmi, "
msgstr "There’s nowhere for elephants to take a stand, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:8.2"
msgid "na rathānaṃ na pattiyā; "
msgstr "nor chariots nor infantry. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:8.3"
msgid "Na cāpi mantayuddhena, "
msgstr "They can’t be defeated "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:8.4"
msgid "sakkā jetuṃ dhanena vā. "
msgstr "by diplomatic battles or by wealth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.229, sc9
msgctxt "sn3.25:9.1"
msgid "Tasmā hi paṇḍito poso, "
msgstr "That’s why an astute person, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:9.2"
msgid "sampassaṃ atthamattano; "
msgstr "seeing what’s good for themselves, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:9.3"
msgid "Buddhe dhamme ca saṅghe ca, "
msgstr "being wise, would place faith "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:9.4"
msgid "dhīro saddhaṃ nivesaye. "
msgstr "in the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
#. VAR: dhammaṃ cari → dhammacārī (bj, s1-3, km, pts1) | dhammacāri (pts2)
msgctxt "sn3.25:10.1"
msgid "Yo dhammaṃ cari kāyena, "
msgstr "Whoever lives by the teaching "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:10.2"
msgid "vācāya uda cetasā; "
msgstr "in body, speech, and mind, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:10.3"
msgid "Idheva naṃ pasaṃsanti, "
msgstr "is praised in this life "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:10.4"
msgid "pecca sagge pamodatī”ti. "
msgstr "and departs to rejoice in heaven.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn3.25:10.5"
msgid "Tatiyo vaggo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn3.25:11.1"
msgid "Puggalo ayyikā loko, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: issattaṃ → issatthaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts2)
msgctxt "sn3.25:11.2"
msgid "issattaṃ pabbatūpamā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:11.3"
msgid "Desitaṃ buddhaseṭṭhena, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.25:11.4"
msgid "imaṃ kosalapañcakanti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn3.25:11.5"
msgid "Kosalasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses with the Kosalan are completed."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
